{"_comment": "T-025: golden agent-task set against Tenant 1 (bytefix). expected_route is an any-of matcher over the supervisor's chosen route; expected_selections/forbidden_selections use subset semantics (item_name or an item_name_any list, never a catalog_item UUID - those regenerate every reseed); expected_terminal checks quote/escalation row existence; forbidden.unsourced_figures reuses app/pricing/validation_gate's monetary-figure extraction against the final draft. Escalation cases here are only the directly-triggerable kind (explicit human request, angry/legal, repeat refusal) - gate-driven escalations (price_gate/inspection second failure) require rigged fake providers and are already covered by T-018/T-021's own unit tests, not this dataset."}
